Authored by etiennemeleard Parent: 3953 2016-06-07 09:47 Allow to configure client stalling detection.
Related config parameter is "stalling_detection", it may be :
- A true boolean to enable detection with default behaviour : $config['stalling_detection'] = true;
- An array including any of the following values (all optional) : count_divergence : the maximum chunk count a worker can be late over the global average (last 5 chunks of every worker) duration_divergence : the maximum ratio between a process's current upload time and the global average (last 5 chunks of every worker) automatic_retries : the number of times the upload is resumed transparently before asking the user if he/she wants to keep going
Full version is (those are also the default values) :
$config['stalling_detection'] = array( 'count_divergence' => 10, 'duration_divergence' => 7, 'automatic_retries' => 3 );
- A false boolean to turn off detection : $config['stalling_detection'] = false;

