Example of use: if you have a filesender install where you _only_ want to see big files, you should be able to decline transfers < 100 MB.

Also useful for creating blacklists of users.

Changeset alert by etiennemeleard in project FileSender 

.............................................................................

Add a way to specify custom transfer validator to conduct further checks after usual checks (size, number of recipients ...)

This is configured using the transfer_validators configuration parameter which must be an array of callables.

Each test gets the transfer object as sole argument and can either return false (reject without reason given) or throw a standard exception with a translatable id as message (messages can easily be
translated in config lang files overrides).

Example :

$config['transfer_validators'] = array(
    function($transfer) {
        $blacklist = array_filter(explode("\n", file_get_contents(FILESENDER_BASE.'/config/blacklist.txt')));

        return !in_array(Auth::user()->id, $blacklist);
    },
    function($transfer) {
        if(!count(array_filter($transfer->files, function($file) {
            return $file->size > 10 * 1024 * 1024;
        })))
            throw new Exception('you_must_have_at_least_one_file_over_10mb');
    }
);



